fct_lump: n or prop

### n
starwars %>% 
 mutate(skin_color = (fct_lump(fct_inorder(skin_color), n = 5))) %>% 
 ggplot(.,aes(x=skin_color)) +
 geom_bar() +
 coord_flip()

### prop
starwars %>% 
 mutate(skin_color = fct_lump(skin_color, prop = .01, other_level = "extra")) %>% 
 count(skin_color,sort=T)
### mean
starwars %>%
  mutate(skin_color = fct_lump(skin_color, n = 6)) %>%
  group_by(skin_color) %>%
  summarise(mean_mass = mean(mass, na.rm = TRUE))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

fct_reorder

# When you wish to reorder by another variable
starwars %>% 
  mutate(eye_color = fct_reorder(eye_color, skin_color)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = skin_color, y = eye_color)) + 
  geom_col()

# When you wish to reorder by another variable
starwars %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(eye_color=fct_shuffle(eye_color)) %>% 
  .[["eye_color"]] %>% 
  levels
##  [1] "blue"          "yellow"        "black"         "red"          
##  [5] "brown"         "pink"          "blue-gray"     "orange"       
##  [9] "green, yellow" "white"         "gold"          "unknown"      
## [13] "dark"          "hazel"         "red, blue"
# Relevel
starwars %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(eye_color=fct_relevel(eye_color,c("hazel","pink"))) %>%  # hazel, pink, everything...
  .[["eye_color"]] %>% 
  levels
##  [1] "hazel"         "pink"          "black"         "blue"         
##  [5] "blue-gray"     "brown"         "dark"          "gold"         
##  [9] "green, yellow" "orange"        "red"           "red, blue"    
## [13] "unknown"       "white"         "yellow"
# Reverse order
starwars %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(eye_color=fct_rev(eye_color)) %>% 
  .[["eye_color"]] %>% 
  levels
##  [1] "yellow"        "white"         "unknown"       "red, blue"    
##  [5] "red"           "pink"          "orange"        "hazel"        
##  [9] "green, yellow" "gold"          "dark"          "brown"        
## [13] "blue-gray"     "blue"          "black"

# Lump
starwars %>%   dplyr::mutate(lumped=forcats::fct_lump(skin_color,n=5))

Concatenate

fa <- factor("a")
fb <- factor("b")
fab <- factor(c("a", "b"))
fct_c(fa, fb, fab)
## [1] a b a b
## Levels: a b

Cross

# Combine two different things:
fruit <- factor(c("apple", "kiwi", "apple", "apple"))
colour <- factor(c("green", "green", "red", "green"))
eaten <- c("yes", "no", "yes", "no")

fct_cross(fruit, colour)
## [1] apple:green kiwi:green  apple:red   apple:green
## Levels: apple:green kiwi:green apple:red
fct_cross(fruit, colour, eaten)
## [1] apple:green:yes kiwi:green:no   apple:red:yes   apple:green:no 
## Levels: apple:green:no kiwi:green:no apple:green:yes apple:red:yes
fct_cross(fruit, colour, keep_empty = TRUE)
## [1] apple:green kiwi:green  apple:red   apple:green
## Levels: apple:green kiwi:green apple:red kiwi:red
